President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the nation. This comes as COVID-19 infections across the country continue to rise. Editor's note: This event is also live on DStv 403. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing the nation on developments in relation to the country’s response to the coronavirus pandemic. READ: Ramaphosa, NCCC to meet stakeholders over COVID-19 spike The address follows meetings of the National Coronavirus Command Council (NCCC), the President’s Coordinating Council (PCC) and Cabinet. President Ramaphosa also hosted a virtual engagement on Sunday between government and interfaith leaders on the COVID-19 Risk-Adjusted Strategy in an attempt to strengthen the national effort responding to the shifting pandemic.